page.title: 16The Landslip
page.content: {The Landslip}is between{Shanklin}and{ {Bonchurch.}It is near a place called {Luccombe}.It is very hilly.There is are places called{Devils Chimney, {Criss-cross cottage}and there is a {castle.}You can see for a long way out to sea.{Devils Chimney}is a big rock that has split over the years. Some men put some steps in it, and it is very steep and narrow. The walls were very crumbly. It is stony and very damp and there are bars to hold on to.There are lots of trees and there are ivy bushs,sycamore and holly and twigs and blue-bells elder, fern, nettles and hawthorn and cow-parsley. It is called the{Landslip}because the whole area is slowly slipping downwards into the sea,it is constantly on the move.
